	<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm">
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Centre_of_mass  
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass">
A <b>Centre_of_mass</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Shape_dependent_property_representation"/> that represents the point characterizing a center of mass in a geometric coordinate space.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Centre_of_mass  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass.wr:WR1">
The associated representation shall contain only one item.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Centre_of_mass  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass.wr:WR2">
The only item of the associated representation shall be a <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/>, locating the considered centre of mass.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Centre_of_mass  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Centre_of_mass.wr:WR3">
The <express_ref linkend="Foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation.context_of_items"/> of the associated representation shall be a <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>. 
The centre point is founded in that <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Inertia_matrix_item  
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item">
An <b>Inertia_matrix_item</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/> that specifies the six distinct values of an inertia matrix which represents the angular mass of a rigid body about a particular point and their common unit.
 <p>These six values include three mass moments of inertia about three mass products of inertia about three orthogonal axes through the point in question.</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Inertia_matrix_item  Attribute: inertia_values 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item.inertia_values"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item.inertia_values">
<p>the six distinct values of the inertia matrix, in the following order:
Ixx, Iyy, Izz, Ixy, Iyz, Izx.</p>
<p>x, y and z relate respectively to the first, second and third axis of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/>, according to which the inertia values have been computed.</p>
		<figure id="f1" number="1">
			<title>Matrix of inertia representation</title>
			<img src="axis.gif"/>
		</figure>
<p>Figure 1 shows the spatial representation of the matrix of inertia of a rigid body.</p>
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Inertia_matrix_item  Attribute: common_unit 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item.common_unit"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item.common_unit">
the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/> in which the inertia values are expressed.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Moments_of_inertia  
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia">
A <b>Moments_of_inertia</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Shape_dependent_property_representation"/> which measures the solid's ability to resist changes in rotational speed about a specific axis.
<p>The moment of inertia of a body is not only related to its mass but also the distribution of the mass throughout the body. So two bodies of the same mass may possess different moments of inertia.</p>
		<p>The matrix of inertia is specified with respect to a particular <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/> that identifies the axes along which the inertia values have been computed.</p>
		<p>Ixx, Iyy and Izz are called the moments of inertia while Ixy, Iyx, Iyz, Izy, Izx and Ixz are the products of inertia.</p>
		<figure id="f2" number="2">
			<title>Example of rigid body.</title>
			<img src="moi_01.gif"/>
		</figure>
		<figure id="f3" number="3">
			<title>Mathematical formulas of the moments and products of inertia.</title>
			<img src="moi_02.gif"/>
		</figure>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Moments_of_inertia  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia.wr:WR1">
The associated representation shall contain only one <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Moments_of_inertia  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia.wr:WR2">
The associated representation shall contain one <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Inertia_matrix_item"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Inertia_characteristics_arm  Entity: Moments_of_inertia  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="Inertia_characteristics:arm:Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Inertia_characteristics_arm.Moments_of_inertia.wr:WR3">
The <express_ref linkend="Foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation.context_of_items"/> of the associated representation shall be a <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>. 
The <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/> is founded in that <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
